HEADWORD: Haggada
<hw>Hag*ga"da</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧g*g⟦aum⟧"d⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Haggadoth</plw> <pr>(-d⟦omac⟧th)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Rabbinic <ets>hagg⟦amac⟧dh⟦amac⟧</ets>, fr. Heb.
<ets>higg⟦imac⟧dh</ets> to relate.]</ety> <def>A story, anecdote, or
legend in the Talmud, to explain or illustrate the text of the Old
Testament.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>hagada</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
